{"type":"message","id":"a150e0a4","parentId":"68a17e17","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:46:48.365Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_09ron0agtbn1_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5190\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2939\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 014614 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step, but I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs and create the classifier implementation. This is a concrete file creation that enables the experiment.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"warm-nudibranch","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5190\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2939\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 014614 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step, but I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs and create the classifier implementation. This is a concrete file creation that enables the experiment.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331208364}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f9fa6dd","parentId":"a150e0a4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:46:48.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_09ron0agtbn1_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 014515\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals document:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Next priority: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next action should be implementing the TIC classifier on pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSo the next concrete action should be to implement the TIC classifier. This involves creating a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the logs directory and create the TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nThe most direct way to advance this is to create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structures (goals, docs, architecture patterns that persist)\r\n3. Identifies variant structures (specific content, findings, mutations)\r\n4. Tests classification accuracy\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script `tic_classifier.ps1` that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant structures across pulse logs. The pulse logs contain patterns (goals structure, doc references, architecture insights) that persist vs specific mutations/findings that change each session.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements Temporal Invariance Compression by analyzing pulse logs, classifying content as invariant (stable across sessions) vs variant (session-specific), and testing prediction accuracy on next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Implements compression-causal duality: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinInvariantCount = 2,\r\n    [float]$MinMatchScore = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$logDir = \"logs\"\r\n$invariantDoc = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\"\r\n\r\n# Get pulse logs sorted by time\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $logDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 3) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Need at least 3 pulse logs for TIC experiment\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs for invariance...\"\r\n\r\n# Parse pulse content into structured components\r\nfunction Parse-PulseComponents($content) {\r\n    $components = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Files = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Mutations = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals mentioned\r\n    if ($content -match '(?s)## Goals.*?(?=##|\\Z)') {\r\n        $components.Goals = [regex]::Matches($_, '\\b(?:Phase \\d|Active|Completed|Pending)[^\\n]*') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $components.Files = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?:`[^`]+`|[A-Z][a-z]+(?:[A-Z][a-z]+)*(?:\\.[a-z]+)?)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights (lines with key findings, insights, hypothesis)\r\n    $components.Insights = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(?:insight|key finding|hypothesis):[^\\n]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract actions (lines starting with - [ ])\r\n    $components.Actions = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^\\s*-\\s*\\[[ x]\\]\\s*[^\\n]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract mutations applied\r\n    if ($content -match '(?s)### MUTATION(.*?)```') {\r\n        $components.Mutations = $matches[1] -split \"`n\" | Where-Object { $_ -match 'file:|old_text:|new_text:' }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $components\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract n-gram features from text\r\nfunction Get-TextFeatures($text) {\r\n    $features = @{}\r\n    $words = [regex]::Split($text.ToLower(), '\\W+') | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }\r\n    \r\n    # Unigrams\r\n    foreach ($word in $words) {\r\n        $features[$word] = 1\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Bigrams\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $words.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n        $bigram = $words[$i] + \"_\" + $words[$i + 1]\r\n        $features[$bigram] = 1\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Parse all pulse logs\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += @{\r\n        Name = $log.Name\r\n        Components = Parse-PulseComponents $content\r\n        Features = Get-TextFeatures $content\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Parsed $($pulses.Count) pulses\"\r\n\r\n# Identify invariant features (appear in >= MinInvariantCount pulses)\r\n$featureCounts = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pul\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:45:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331208365}}
