{"type":"message","id":"84ad0086","parentId":"101e765c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:47:34.757Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_eo74tfjtq1mi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TIC Experiment Results - 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32  03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap  more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":468,"aggregated":"# TIC Experiment Results - 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32  03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap  more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331254755}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d6ad5f4","parentId":"84ad0086","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:47:42.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the context. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment has been run and results show:\n- 90% precision and 88.5% recall for invariant classification\n- TIC Score: 2/3 (SUPPORTED)\n- Next experiment: embedding-based compressor\n\nThe pulse log I just read shows a proposed mutation to create `tic_classifier.ps1` but it was rejected because:\n- \"Rejected: the (missing)\" - the old_text \"(new file)\" doesn't match any existing content\n\nThe sandbox agent was trying to create a NEW file, but the mutation system seems to require an old_text that matches something existing. This is a limitation of the mutation system - it can't create new files, only edit existing ones.\n\n\nThe classifier was being proposed to implement the next embedding-based compressor experiment. Now I'm checking what the agent actually accomplished this cycle - it appears no mutations were applied, but there was a response with an observation and action to create the classifier file.","thinkingSignature":"9812a2836fb0471503c8a7406bfcc7c2956f59918020d2498670bc4f6d204aaf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ij580r90iu3c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\" -Raw","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8171,"output":261,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20386,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774331254757}}
{"type":"message","id":"80f00c03","parentId":"7d6ad5f4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:47:42.936Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ij580r90iu3c_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\r\n**Status:** READY TO RUN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```powershell\r\nGet-ChildItem logs/*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\nFor each pulse, extract:\r\n- Topic keywords (nouns/verbs)\r\n- File references\r\n- Question marks (open problems)\r\n- Action items (verbs in imperative)\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Compute Invariants\r\nFind features that persist across multiple pulses (invariant = appears in �%�3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Compute Variants\r\nFind features unique to single pulses or clusters (variant = appears in <3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 5: Predict Next Pulse\r\nUsing invariant/variant classification, predict which features appear in pulse N+1.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% next-pulse feature recall\r\n\r\n## Log Inventory\r\n| Pulse | Date | Key Content |\r\n|-------|------|-------------|\r\n| (to be populated) | | |\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD)\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Implementation\n\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Invariant/Variant classification accuracy: >70%\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\n\n## Data\n- Source: `logs/pulse_*.md` (20+ pulse logs)\n- Target: Last pulse is `pulse_2026-03-23 145438.md`\n```"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":498,"aggregated":"# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\r\n**Status:** READY TO RUN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```powershell\r\nGet-ChildItem logs/*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\nFor each pulse, extract:\r\n- Topic keywords (nouns/verbs)\r\n- File references\r\n- Question marks (open problems)\r\n- Action items (verbs in imperative)\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Compute Invariants\r\nFind features that persist across multiple pulses (invariant = appears in �%�3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Compute Variants\r\nFind features unique to single pulses or clusters (variant = appears in <3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 5: Predict Next Pulse\r\nUsing invariant/variant classification, predict which features appear in pulse N+1.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% next-pulse feature recall\r\n\r\n## Log Inventory\r\n| Pulse | Date | Key Content |\r\n|-------|------|-------------|\r\n| (to be populated) | | |\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD)\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Implementation\n\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Invariant/Variant classification accuracy: >70%\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\n\n## Data\n- Source: `logs/pulse_*.md` (20+ pulse logs)\n- Target: Last pulse is `pulse_2026-03-23 145438.md`\n```","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331262935}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c5e75be","parentId":"80f00c03","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:47:55.019Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize the pulse cycle:\n\n**Pulse 2026-03-24 014515 Summary:**\n\n1. **No mutations applied** - the proposed mutation was rejected because it tried to create a new file `tic_classifier.ps1` but the mutation format requires old_text to match existing content, and \"(new file)\" doesn't match anything.\n\n2. **What was attempted:** The agent proposed creating `tic_classifier.ps1` to implement the next TIC experiment (embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU)\n\n3. **Status:** The agent is working through Phase 1-2 of the Breakaway sandbox project, specifically advancing the TIC research line","thinkingSignature":"766417f3e64aebe12a4bf7437ff015e22075f36cd074a4b0c8430d9d7d569808"},{"type":"text","text":"\n## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 01:45 AM\n\n### Result: ⚠️ Mutation Rejected (no changes applied)\n\n**What Happened:**\nThe sandbox LLM analyzed the current state and identified the **TIC experiment** as the next priority. It proposed creating `tic_classifier.ps1` to implement an embedding-based compressor to test whether causal structure = invariant structure. However, the mutation was **rejected** because the mutation system requires `old_text` to match existing file content — `(new file)` doesn't match anything, so new files can't be created via mutation.\n\n**Current Research Status:**\n- TIC initial experiment: ✅ Complete (90% precision, 88.5% recall, TIC Score 2/3 SUPPORTED)\n- Next step: Embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- That next step requires creating new files, which the current mutation system can't do\n\n**State:** Agent is blocked on file creation. The mutation pipeline needs a workaround — either creating files through the LLM response output directly, or modifying the mutation mechanism to support new file creation. The agent correctly identified the right next action but couldn't execute it through the mutation interface."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8826,"output":385,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21165,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774331262937}}
